antithymocytic globulin (n = 395) produced the same malignancy incidence (0.54%) 
as with cyclosporin (n = 685; 0.60%). On the other hand, malignant tumours 
occurred much earlier under cyclosporin than under azathioprine/antithymocytic 
globulin (27 and 68 months, respectively).

